being disciplined in the present can certainly be seen as a privilege because it requires a certain level of self-awareness, self-control, and the ability to delay gratification. By making choices that prioritize your future goals and well-being over short-term desires, you are investing in your future and setting yourself up for success.

For example, if you are disciplined with your spending habits and prioritize saving money, you can build a financial cushion that can help you weather unexpected expenses or pursue opportunities in the future. If you are disciplined with your health habits, such as exercising regularly and eating a balanced diet, you can reduce your risk of chronic disease and improve your overall quality of life in the long run.

Ultimately, being disciplined in the present can be a powerful tool for achieving your goals, realizing your dreams, and creating a better future for yourself.

Como pareja comprometida no solo en los negocios, sino también en el desarrollo personal, reconocemos la importancia de prepararnos no solo mentalmente, sino también físicamente. La Spartan Race nos brindó la oportunidad de fusionar estas dos facetas de nuestra vida.

La preparación física se convirtió en una metáfora poderosa para nuestra preparación en el mundo de los negocios.
